\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\fs24 IDE - Integrated Development Environment\ul\fs28\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1080\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\fs24 IDE's are software that specialize in helping you program\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 IDE's can help by:\ul\fs28\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1440\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\fs24 Linting - pointing out syntax or format errors\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 Allowing you to install online add-ons that can further enhance your programming experience\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 Assistance with debugging issues\ul\fs28\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\fs24 IDE's such as Spyder, Jupyter, Vim, Thonny, Atom, and Sublime are great choices\fs28 . \fs24 However, the IDE we'll use is PyCharm\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 We'll need to install Python first before we can use PyCharm. Use this link to install the latest version of Python: {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://www.python.org/downloads/ }}{\fldrslt{https://www.python.org/downloads/\ul0\cf0}}}}\ul\f0\fs28\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1080\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\fs24 This website should automatically detect the type of operating system you're using\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 Click on the yellow Download Python (version number) for the latest stable version of Python\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 Once the you download the file, open it and check the "Install launcher for all users (recommended) and Add Python (version number) to PATH checkboxes\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 Click on Install Now once you're ready\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 After a short installation session, the wizard will ask if you want ot Disable path length limit. Click on this option when ready. \ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 Once the wizard states that the setup was successful, you can close the wizard\ul\fs28\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\ulnone\fs24 You can open Git Bash and type in "python --version" to know what version of Python is running on your machine\ul\fs28\par

